"'''Things That Never Cross a Man's Mind'''" is a song written by [[Tim Johnson (songwriter)|Tim Johnson]], Don Poythress and [[Wynn Varble]], and recorded by [[United States|American]] [[country music|country]] artist [[Kellie Pickler]]. It was released as the third and final single from her debut album, ''[[Small Town Girl (album)|Small Town Girl]]''. 

The song is part of the tracklist for ''[[Now That's What I Call Country]]''.

==Content==
"Things That Never Cross a Man's Mind" is an up-tempo song, featuring electric guitar and piano in the production. The song's female narrator playfully describes the differences between men and women by stating things that the average woman thinks of on a regular basis, "that never cross[es] a man's mind." Ironically, the song was written by three men.

==Reception==
[[Billboard (magazine)|''Billboard'' magazine]] described the song as "a frisky uptempo number that captures the playful side of Pickler's personality. Men will chuckle and women will nod in agreement. It's a clever lyric with a catchy melody, and Pickler's performance is absolute perfection. She has personality to spare, and this lighthearted single is tailor-made for country radio."<ref>[http://www.billboard.com/bbcom/content_display/reviews/singles/e3ibe8ec7c980d6765cdb1335cee2c66846 Review - Billboard]</ref>

==Chart performance==
The song debuted at number 59 on the U.S. ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' [[Hot Country Songs]] chart for the week of September 10, 2007.<ref>[{{BillboardURLbyName|artist=kellie pickler|chart=all}} Billboard - Kellie Pickler]</ref>
